I’ll try not to make this long… but there really is so much to say about 2022. 1 being…this was by far the hardest year I think I’ve had in a long time. Lots of lessons, mistakes, regrets, hurt, anger, struggle, mental strain but I definitely would be lying if I said this year didn’t have some amazing times as well. Filled with lots of laughs, love, good people, beautiful countries, insane crowds, delicious food and relationships I’ll treasure for a lifetime. I’ve accomplished a lot this year. In my career and within myself, but I haven’t really even scratched the surface of what could be… I’m committed to bettering myself all around all 2023. No more words needed, you’ll see…😏
Thank y’all for supporting and just loving me through it all.. this life is not easy…let’s spread the love we hope to receive❤️
Happy New Year🫶🏼

All this and joy will surround you as long as you got me…-Notice me ✨

Thank you God!…

Y’all don’t know how many times I tried to post this already… 🤦🏽‍♀️ I wrote out everything again and again so here it is …hopefully this posts…

Now I know I’m mad late… but I need to sit with this one for a second. God is so GOOD.
FENTYBOWL BABY!!! WE MF DID THAT!!
My first Super Bowl and it was with @badgalriri ??! Blessed is not even the word for it. Thank you God for getting me to this point… it was challenging and probably the hardest thing I’ve done but all worth it in the end. A 60 ft Platform?? And moving??? I never thought I’d ever dance on a roller coaster but I just keep surprising myself🤣
@parrisgoebel I can’t say thank you enough for having me be a part of histoRIH!! We are all gonna look back at this performance for years and years to come!! You’re an absolute genius and you should be beyond proud of the magic you created!! ❤️
@gab.robert & @nat_bat_ Y’all stay holding it DOWN!!! The dream team, thank you!🫶🏼
To ALL the dancers that pour their blood, sweat, and tears into this performance… WE ATE DOWNNN, DEVOURED, AND LICKED THE PLATE CLEAN. There was an immense amount of hard work, late nights, and focus that came with the process and to to see everyone pull through it together was really cool. You should be so PROUD! This was a huge cast but I loved seeing old faces and meetings new ones! I’m a quiet person but I’ve taken in so much on this job. Thank you y’all for a dope Super Bowl run! 
Special shout-out to @starleyanne on my left up there on that platform! We were scared kinda till the end but I couldn’t have done it without you!! Literally… because every time I wanted to talk myself out of it Starley wouldnt let me 😂🙏🏼 
Also to all the platform ladies… Quite literally, If not us then who?? Because 60 ft. is crazy!!🤣 It was amazing spending this time and sharing this experience with y’all! First 14 people in the world to do this and we made it look effortless. Much love😘
And to everyone else a part of this production y’all killed it! Especially those who always kept us protected and safe up there!🙏🏼

Meet Jordan Laza (@j_o_r_t_a_y), rising backup dancer taking the commercial scene by storm.✨

In 2021, her profile skyrocketed after she performed @NicoleKirkland’s choreography to Chris Brown’s “Under the Influence” in a viral class video. 

Since then, she has danced backup for @DojaCat, @ChloeBailey and the @SavagexFenty Show Vol. 4, to name a few. 

Laza melds her varied training, which spans ballet, contemporary, hip hop and jazz, into a flavor all her own, commanding space with effortless strength and electrifying presence.

Head to the link in our bio to learn more about Laza's limitless potential.

Story by @lydia.l.murray 
📸: @j_o_r_t_a_y by @Jamal.Peters, Courtesy Laza

Here we go… last show of this leg of The Scarlet Tour in Chicago tonight. What an experience this whole tour has been. Filled with lots of great moments and lessons that I’m super thankful to take away with me. I’m super blessed to be where I’m at with the people I’m with. The biggest thank you to  @ebonywilliamsworld @ardundundun @theresastone91 for all of it..you have no idea how grateful I am.
And my dancers that I had the pleasure to share the stage with, your talent, your support, your love, your laughs, and understanding is so appreciated..WE MF DID IT, and it’s just the start. And Last but certainly not least… Amala.. Ms. Doja Cat herself.. I am so so freaking proud of you! Your first Arena tour!! Man you’re such an undeniable talent and such a beautiful person. I’m so honored to be a part of this magic you create. To many many more successes and tours, I’ll ride with you till the wheels fall off ❤️🥹 @dojacat
